.TH BOTTOM 1 "2026-07-23" "bottom" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bottom \- log process starts and stops
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bottom
[
.I options
]
.br
.B bottom trace
[
.I options
]
.B --
.I command
[
.I arguments
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bottom
is a read-only process watcher. It writes readable Start, Exec, Stop, and Gap lines to standard output.
.PP
Redirect standard output with the shell when a log file is wanted.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B watch
Watch the process table. This is also the default when no command is supplied.
.TP
.B trace
Start one command directly and watch it and its observed descendants.
.TP
.B version
Print version, source commit, and build date.
.TP
.B completion
Write fish completions to standard output.
.SH OPTIONS
Run
.B bottom -h
or
.B bottom trace -h
for the complete option list and defaults.
.PP
.B -tui
explicitly selects the interactive display instead of the readable event log.
.PP
.B -parent-exe
includes the parent executable name in a fixed-width column. It is enabled by default in the TUI and disabled by default in readable line output. Use
.B -parent-exe=false
to hide it in the TUI.
.PP
.B -ppid
includes a parent PID column in readable process event lines and TUI views.
.PP
.B -backend
defaults to auto. Native choices are
.BR linux-proc-connector ,
.BR windows-etw ,
and
.BR macos-endpoint-security .
.B poll
selects process-table polling.
.SH OUTPUT
The default log format is:
.PP
.nf
Start: PID      command
Exec:  PID      command
Stop:  PID      command
.fi
.PP
With
.BR -ppid ,
process lines use
.B "Start: PID      PARENT_PID      command"
and the corresponding Exec and Stop forms.
.PP
With
.BR -parent-exe ,
the fixed-width parent executable name appears after the optional parent PID and before the unbounded command.
.SH SECURITY
bottom observes processes but does not act on them. Trace starts only the command supplied after
.BR -- .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ps (1),
.BR top (1)
